especially when the tank is more than half full
vapor emissions occur at all times
fuel tank leaks when filling up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to collapse or become undrivable, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's air suspension system leaks
causing the vehicle to sag or collapse

especially after sitting for an extended period; the vehicle is unable to maintain its normal ride height; the air suspension system fails to auto-level the vehicle; the vehicle's handling and suspension performance are compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the catalytic converter can lead to increased emissions, decreased fuel efficiency, and potential engine damage. It can also cause the "check engine" light to illuminate, leading to costly repairs and potential safety hazards.
A camshaft gasket leak can cause a major oil leak, leading to engine seizure and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
